Obituary Chicago Tribune 04/15/2009
Lucille R. Locascio, nee Canzolino, age 87, beloved wife of the late Albert; devoted mother of Sal (Anna) and Frank (Sandra); fond grandmother of Frank, Valerie, Gina, Donna, Anthony and Mark; great-grandmother of seven; dear sister of Jennie (the late Vince) Boffa, Angelina Fontana, the late Vito Canzolino and the late Anthony (Florence) Canzolino; dear aunt and great-aunt of many. Funeral Friday, April 17, 2009, 8:30 a.m. from Salerno's Rosedale Chapels, Joseph A. Russo Funeral Director, 450 W. Lake St., Roselle (3/4 mile West of Bloomingdale/Roselle Roads), to Mary, Queen of Heaven Church, 426 N. West, Elmhurst. Mass 10 a.m. Entombment Queen of Heaven Cemetery Main Mausoleum. Visitation Thursday, April 16, 3 to 9 p.m. For info, 630-889-1700. Please omit flowers. In lieu of flowers, donations to The Disabled American Veterans would be appreciated.

Obituary Chicago Tribune 08/15/2008
Anthony Canzolino, 86, of Elmhurst. Beloved husband of Florence, nee Vertucci; loving father of Marilyn (John) Loster, Frank (Carol) Canzolino and the late Diana (Larry) Mullally; dearest grandfather of John Loster, Anthony (Gina) Loster and Adrienne Canzolino; great-grandfather of Breanna, Julia, Kyle, Sarah and Rachel; fond brother of Jenny Boffa, Lucille Locascio, Angie Fontana and the late Vito Canzolino; also survived by many nieces and nephews. Visitation 3 to 9 p.m. with a Funeral Service at 7 p.m. Friday at Humes Funeral Home, 320 W. Lake St., Addison (2 mi. E. of Rt. 53, 2 mi. W. of Rt. 83). Cremation Private. If desired memorials to the Diabetes Assoc. appreciated. For info www.HumesFuneralHome.com or 630-628-8808

Russo Funeral Director, 450 W. Lake St., Roselle (3/4 mile West Bloomingdale/Roselle Rd.). Chapel service to be celebrated at 10:30 a.m. Entombment Queen of Heaven Cemetery, Crucifixion Garden Mausoleum. Visitation Sunday, August 17th, 3 to 9 p.m. 630-889-1700. Please omit flowers. In lieu of flowers all donations will be forwarded to the Susan G. Komen Cancer Foundation.

Obituary Times-Picayune, The (New Orleans, LA) June 28, 2003
Dorothy E. McDaniels, a real estate title abstractor, died Thursday at her home. She was 75. Mrs. McDaniels was born in Chicago and lived in New Orleans for the past 37 years. She was an elder at Canal Street Presbyterian Church. Survivors include three sons, Mark E., Christopher L. and Eric S. McDaniels; two sisters, June Hansen and Constance Nissen; and nine grandchildren. A memorial service will be held Sunday at 2 p.m. at Canal Street Presbyterian Church, 4302 Canal St. Jacob Schoen & Son Funeral Home handled arrangements.

Obituary Daily Herald (Arlington Heights, IL) January 24 & 25, 2004

She was the beloved daughter of Anna (nee Manna) and Philip; loving sister of Rosalie (Bill) Logsdon; dear aunt of Philip (Lorie) Logsdon, Susan (Darryl) Lesniak and LeeAnn (Thomas) McCartney; and great-aunt of eight. Friends may visit www.dailyherald.com/obits to express condolences and sign the guest book. For funeral information, (847)685-1002.
